Hayat also said numerous security forces were not in uniform, which may have caused some confusion about their identities. USA military officials confirmed that local security personnel aligned with Afghan government forces had been killed.

Lakers reportedly competing with Cavs to sign Derrick Rose

With the National Basketball Association offseason winding down, there hasn't been as many Lakers rumors going around.  According to a report from Adrian Wojnarowski at ESPN , Kyrie Irving wants to be traded to the San Antonio Spurs .

Microsoft is bringing down 'Fancy Bear' hackers with IP lawyers

The efforts are already having an effect, as Fancy Bear has started switching to names that are a little more general. The action, though, is not about dragging the hackers into court.

Preliminary findings suggest Navy at fault in Fitzgerald collision, report says

The two ships collided on the Fitzgerald's starboard side directly next to the berthing area, where sailors sleep. One told CNN that a "slew of things" went wrong, including not doing anything until the last second.

Linkin Park's Chester Bennington dead at 41

Just dealing with a range of emotions today. "I was watching a video of the two performing together and it was heartbreaking". With lines like "tired of being what you want me to be", it features Bennington at his most vulnerable and hurt.






