Worth Watching Stock Turquoise Hill Resources Ltd. (TRQ)

By Adam Smith -  Jul 19, 2017 0 7 









Many analysts are providing their Estimated Earnings analysis for Turquoise Hill Resources Ltd. and for the current quarter 5 analysts have projected that the stock could give an Average Earnings estimate of $-0.01/share. These analysts have also projected a Low Estimate of $-0.04/share and a High Estimate of $0.02/share.




In case of Revenue Estimates, 3 analysts have provided their consensus Average Revenue Estimates for Turquoise Hill Resources Ltd. as 222.8 Million. According to these analysts, the Low Revenue Estimate for Turquoise Hill Resources Ltd. is 200.83 Million and the High Revenue Estimate is 261.56 Million. The company had Year Ago Sales of 329.7 Million.
These analysts also forecasted Growth Estimates for the Current Quarter for TRQ to be -200%. They are projecting Next Quarter growth of 50%. For the next 5 years, Turquoise Hill Resources Ltd. is expecting Growth of 2% per annum, whereas in the past 5 years the growth was 19.52% per annum.
Some buy side analysts are also providing their Analysis on Turquoise Hill Resources Ltd., where 1 analysts have rated the stock as Strong buy, 2 analysts have given a Buy signal, 3 said it’s a HOLD, 0 reported it as Underperform and 0 analysts rated the stock as Sell. (These Recommendations are for the Current Month Only reported by Yahoo Finance.)
When it comes to the Analysis of a Stock, Price Target plays a vital role. Analysts reported that the Price Target for Turquoise Hill Resources Ltd. might touch $6.5 high while the Average Price Target and Low price Target is $5.71 and $4.5 respectively.

Turquoise Hill Resources Ltd. closed its last trading session at $2.92 with the loss of -2.4%. The Market Capitalization of the company stands at 5.58 Billion. The Company has 52-week high of $3.80 and 52-week low of $2.44. The stock’s current distance from 20-Day Simple Moving Average (SMA20) is 6.92% where SMA50 and SMA200 are 7.62% and -7.41% respectively. The Company Touched its 52-Week High on 02/02/17 and 52-Week Low on 06/05/17.
The Relative Volume of the company is 1.28 and Average Volume (3 months) is 3.33 million. Turquoise Hill Resources Ltd. P/E (price to earnings) ratio is 43.18 and Forward P/E ratio of 0.
The company shows its Return on Assets (ROA) value of 1.1%. The Return on Equity (ROE) value stands at 1.5%. While it’s Return on Investment (ROI) value is 1%.




While looking at the Stock’s Performance, Turquoise Hill Resources Ltd. currently shows a Weekly Performance of 2.52%, where Monthly Performance is 14.92%, Quarterly performance is 2.89%, 6 Months performance is -16.67% and yearly performance percentage is -19.26%. Year to Date performance value (YTD perf) value is -11.76%. The Stock currently has a Weekly Volatility of 2.78% and Monthly Volatility of 3.23%.
 








 
